    <p>Malaysian glove-maker Top Glove de­fended its record with worker wel­fare, say­ing it spent RM20 mil­lion (S$6.6 mil­lion) to im­prove ac­com­mo­da­tion for its fac­tory work­ers in the last two months. The com­pany is un­der the spot­light fol­low­ing a ma­jor Covid-19 out­break at its Se­lan­gor fac­to­ries and dor­mi­to­ries.</p>

